args:
We have reconnoitered the area
thoroughly and have yet to find a single
person. This is fruitless. Have you turned
up any clues, Mitsuhide?

Yeah, I've got one piece of good news.
There was food in that teahouse. The other
shops were all full to bursting with meat
and fish and rice and whatnot, too.
Conventional wisdom dictates that where\nthere is food, there are people, and yet...

Hm. At the very least, we'll not want for
sustenance. I admit I was rather ill
entertaining the thought of starving to
death.
All this walking about has me quite\nfamished. Perhaps I'll stop in for a bite\nat the teahouse.
You still seem pretty downcast,\nNobunaga. What's on your mind?
I should think the source of my distress\nobvious! We are no closer to discovering a\nmeans of egress from this empty prison!

I dream of unifying the lands of Hinomoto!
Of becoming shogun! And those dreams
will crumble to dust if we are left here to
rot!
Come on, we only just got here.\nTake a deep breath and chill out a little.
How could I possibly be ＂chill＂?! I—\nWait! That's it! I know what we could do!
Yes! I'm going back to our world!\nI will avail the power of my soulpact!

Would you cool down for a second,
firebreather? If we could do anything about
this with a dragon's power, Daikokuten
would've already solved the problem.
Yep! For all my power, I'm about as\nuseless as a parasol in a typhoon\nright now!

I'm well aware. My goal is not to escape
outright, but to inform my own dragon,
Susano-o, of our predicament, and have
him assist us!

If I use the power of my soulpact, he
will appear here, using my body as an
intermediary. And then, when I release the
power, he will return to our original world.
Once Susano-o is aware of the situation,\nhe will act to rescue us from our plight!
As ever, you are as sharp as the blade\nyou wield, Nobunaga!
Hark! My ambition to achieve my dream\nwill overcome even this trial! And now...!
Susano-o, I call upon you! Thy fearsome\npower I bid make manifest!
Uh... So... Did I blink and miss something,\nor...?
What do you mean you can't use it?\nLike, Susano-o rejected you?
N-no, that's not it! My call is not reaching\nSusano-o!
Surely you jest! Such a thing ought to be\nimpossible!

Indeed. A Wyrmclan leader and dragon
are inextricably soulbound. No matter
the distance between them, one's call
should reach the other without fail.
So long as one of those souls has not\npassed on, that is...
Could it be that we are...already dead?
My goodness, that IS a frightful notion.
Both of you, dial it back a little.\nYou're overthinking this. We're alive.
And the proof is in the pudding—or, well,\nwhatever you're craving right now, \nNobunaga. You said you were hungry, no?
Ah! You speak true! To think I let my\nanxieties spiral out of control so rapidly...
Look, let's hit the teahouse to\ngrab a drink and calm you down.
A cold drink is exactly what I need right\nnow. That being said, a teacup will not\nsuffice.
Ah, there was a water pail at the\nstorefront. I'll just take this, and...
Wh-whoa! Nobunaga, what are you doing?!
That should serve to cool my head.\nSoulpact or no, I must still act the\npart of a leader.
When I said to ＂chill out,＂ I didn't mean it\nliterally. You'll catch a cold, y'know!\nAnd we can't call a doctor here, either.
Hmph, me? Catch a cold? I have never in\nmy life required the services of a physici—
...Hm? Wait... Mitsuhide. Why do you\nthink we cannot call a doctor?
Er, I mean, there are no people here\nbesides us, right? This is the empty world\nwe were spirited away to, after all.
Suppose that's not necessarily the case.\nAssuming that we vanished from our\nworld and ended up here...
Would the missing shopkeeper couple not\nALSO be here, in the same predicament?

Ah! I think you're onto something! So if
they ARE here, where exactly would they
be? The same place their house was in the
real world?
An appropriate supposition. Mitsuhide!\nShow me the way to that home!
Excuse us, are the man and woman of\nthe house home?!
Ack! P-people?! How?\nWe saw no signs of anyone!
Could it be...that the same thing happened\nto them as to us?!
Wait, what?! Looking at her more closely...\nIs that not Lady Mitsuhide, leader of the\nWyrmclan?!
I-it's true! Why are you here in this world,\nmy lady?!
Based on the way they're speaking,\nthere's little doubt these are the folks\nwho disappeared.
Indeed! Now we have but to escort these\npeople back to our world, and the matter\nwill be resolved!
N-no...! You've come to take us back?!
Please, mercy! I beg you, leave us!
H-hey, calm down! We're in the presence\nof a Wyrmclan leader! Mind your manners!
A-ah! Forgive my impertinence!\nI am unworthy!

Please, my lady, be calm. More
importantly, I would hear your testimony.
It beggars belief, but do you truly not wish
to be returned to the real world?
...Yes. I realize how it sounds, but we\nwish to remain here.
